modules.description: This module defines test execution interfaces for asynchronous test cases, supporting both Lwt-based and synchronous functions. It works with Lwt promises, command-line arguments via Cmdliner, and test suites composed of named test cases with speed annotations. Concrete use cases include writing and running asynchronous tests that require setup/teardown with Lwt_switch or passing configuration through command-line arguments.

This module runs asynchronous test suites with Lwt promises, supporting test cases that require Lwt_switch setup or command-line arguments. It works with Lwt.t, Cmdliner terms, and test lists that include speed annotations. Concrete use cases include testing network clients, file I/O operations, and other asynchronous OCaml code with configurable parameters.
